    "span": "the Warden fell three nights ago. The elders simply haven't said so aloud yet",
    "issue": "The guard claims knowledge of the Warden's death and that the elders are concealing it; this both prematurely reveals a plot point the narrative may withhold and asserts a knowledge state (guard knows a secret truth) that conflicts with the Elder's later authoritative claim."
  },
  {
    "span": "The Warden lives and is in good health; she will address the outpost herself at dusk",
    "issue": "Directly contradicts the guard's earlier statement that the Warden fell three nights ago — the Warden cannot both be dead and alive/in good health, a warden-status identity/knowledge inconsistency."
  }
]

